{
  "texts": [
    "This is achieved by formulating gaugings as topological interfaces in QFT.",
    "2 Similar to the way that topological defects naturally lead to generalized symmetries described by fusion categories as a consequence of basic axioms of QFT (unitarity and locality), considerations of QFT in the presence of topological interfaces immediately produce the algebraic structures of module categories.",
    "Further mathematical structures are encoded in the fusion of the topological interfaces.",
    "In particular the algebra objects arise from the fusion of the corresponding topological interface and its dual, while the fusion between general topological interfaces captures the physics of sequential gauging.",
    "The full fusion structure of interfaces is encapsulated by a groupoid which we refer to as the generalized orbifold groupoid generalizing the work of [46]."
  ]
}